04586nam a22005895i 9780520929630DE-B159720240306123113.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20002000cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209296307 a10.1525/97805209296302doi  a(DE-B1597)649262  a(OCoLC)49570327  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 7aSOC0020102bisacsh04a291.381 aGrimes, Ronald L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aDeeply into the Bone :bRe-Inventing Rites of Passage /cRonald L. Grimes; ed. by Ronald L. Grimes. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2000] 4c©2000  a1 online resource (393 p.) :b6 figures, 7 black-and-white photographs  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aLife Passages00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tList of Figures -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction: Rough Passages, Reinvented Rites -- t1. Celebrating New Life, Ritually Nurturing the Young -- t2. Coming of Age, Joining Up -- t3. Divining Mates, Making Kin -- t4. Living with the Dead, Exiting Gracefully -- t5. Passages,Troubled and Uncharted -- tConclusion: Beyond Passage -- tNotes -- tSources Cited -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOver the past two decades, North Americans have become increasingly interested in understanding and reclaiming the rites that mark significant life passages. In the absence of meaningful rites of passage, we speed through the dangerous intersections of life and often come to regret missing an opportunity to contemplate a child's birth, mark the arrival of maturity, or meditate on the loss of a loved one. Providing a highly personal, thoroughly informed, and cross-cultural perspective on rites of passage for general readers, this book illustrates the power of rites to help us navigate life's troublesome transitions. The work of a major scholar who has spent years writing and teaching about ritual, Deeply into the Bone instigates a conversation in which readers can fruitfully reflect on their own experiences of passage. Covering the significant life events of birth, initiation, marriage, and death, chapters include first-person stories told by individuals who have undergone rites of passage, accounts of practices from around the world, brief histories of selected ritual traditions, and critical reflections probing popular assumptions about ritual. The book also explores innovative rites for other important events such as beginning school, same-sex commitment ceremonies, abortion, serious illness, divorce, and retirement. Taking us confidently into the abyss separating the spiritual from the social scientific, the personal from the scholarly, and the narrative from the analytical, Grimes synthesizes an impressive amount of information to help us find more insightful ways of comprehending life's great transitions. As we face our increasingly complex society, Deeply into the Bone will help us reclaim the power of rites and understand their effect on our lives.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLife change eventsxReligious aspects. 0aRites and ceremonies. 4aAnthropology. 4aCultural & Social. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aGrimes, Ronald L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023675240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092963040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520929630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520929630/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-d